<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Networking Fundamentals — Professional Reference Guide</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:wght@400;600;700&family=IBM+Plex+Sans:wght@300;400;500;600&family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────
   DESIGN TOKENS
───────────────────────────────────────────── */
:root {
  --navy:       #0C1B33;
  --navy-80:    rgba(12,27,51,0.80);
  --navy-10:    rgba(12,27,51,0.06);
  --navy-05:    rgba(12,27,51,0.03);
  --gold:       #B8952A;
  --gold-light: #D4AF55;
  --gold-bg:    rgba(184,149,42,0.08);
  --ink:        #1A2332;
  --ink-60:     #3E4E63;
  --ink-40:     #586578;
  --ink-30:     #7A8799;
  --ink-10:     #E8EDF3;
  --paper:      #FAFBFC;
  --white:      #FFFFFF;
  --rule:       #DDE3EC;

  --accent-1:   #1B4F8A;   /* RJ45   – deep cerulean */
  --accent-2:   #C0410E;   /* Router – burnt sienna  */
  --accent-3:   #2E6B4F;   /* Switch – forest        */
  --accent-4:   #7B3FA0;   /* Webcam – deep violet   */
  --accent-5:   #B8952A;   /* CCTV   – gold          */

  --font-display: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
  --font-body:    'IBM Plex Sans', system-ui, sans-serif;
  --font-mono:    'IBM Plex Mono', 'Courier New', monospace;

  --radius-sm:  4px;
  --radius-md:  8px;
  --radius-lg:  12px;
  --shadow-sm:  0 1px 3px rgba(12,27,51,0.08), 0 1px 2px rgba(12,27,51,0.04);
  --shadow-md:  0 4px 16px rgba(12,27,51,0.10), 0 2px 6px rgba(12,27,51,0.06);
  --shadow-lg:  0 12px 40px rgba(12,27,51,0.14), 0 4px 12px rgba(12,27,51,0.08);
  --transition: 220ms cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
}

/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────
   RESET & BASE
───────────────────────────────────────────── */
*, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
html { scroll-behavior: smooth; font-size: 16px; }

body {
  font-family: var(--font-body);
  background: var(--paper);
  color: var(--ink);
  line-height: 1.65;
  -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  -moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale;
  overflow-x: hidden;
}

/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────
   MASTHEAD
───────────────────────────────────────────── */
.masthead {
  background: var(--navy);
  color: var(--white);
  position: relative;
  overflow: hidden;
}

.masthead::after {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  bottom: 0; left: 0; right: 0;
  height: 3px;
  background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--gold) 0%, var(--gold-light) 50%, var(--gold) 100%);
}

/* subtle topographic line pattern */
.masthead::before {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(
    0deg,
    transparent,
    transparent 39px,
    rgba(255,255,255,0.025) 39px,
    rgba(255,255,255,0.025) 40px
  ),
  repeating-linear-gradient(
    90deg,
    transparent,
    transparent 79px,
    rgba(255,255,255,0.015) 79px,
    rgba(255,255,255,0.015) 80px
  );
  pointer-events: none;
}

.masthead-inner {
  position: relative;
  z-index: 1;
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 52px 48px 48px;
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
  gap: 32px;
  align-items: end;
}

.brand-line {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 14px;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}

.brand-rule {
  width: 32px;
  height: 2px;
  background: var(--gold);
}

.brand-label {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 500;
  letter-spacing: 0.18em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--gold-light);
}

.masthead h1 {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: clamp(36px, 4.5vw, 58px);
  font-weight: 700;
  line-height: 1.08;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  color: var(--white);
  margin-bottom: 14px;
}

.masthead-sub {
  font-size: 15px;
  font-weight: 400;
  color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78);
  letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  max-width: 560px;
}

.masthead-meta {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 10px;
  align-items: flex-end;
  padding-bottom: 4px;
}

.meta-chip {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 500;
  letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  color: var(--gold-light);
  border: 1px solid rgba(184,149,42,0.35);
  border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  padding: 5px 12px;
  white-space: nowrap;
  background: rgba(184,149,42,0.08);
}

/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────
   STATS BAR
───────────────────────────────────────────── */
.stats-bar {
  background: var(--white);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
}

.stats-inner {
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0 48px;
  display: flex;
}

.stat-item {
  flex: 1;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  padding: 20px 16px;
  position: relative;
  gap: 2px;
}

.stat-item + .stat-item::before {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  left: 0; top: 20%; bottom: 20%;
  width: 1px;
  background: var(--rule);
}

.stat-val {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: 28px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--navy);
  line-height: 1;
}

.stat-key {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 500;
  letter-spacing: 0.10em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--ink-30);
}

/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────
   LAYOUT: SIDEBAR + CONTENT
───────────────────────────────────────────── */
.layout {
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 48px 48px 80px;
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 240px 1fr;
  gap: 48px;
  align-items: start;
}

/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────
   SIDEBAR
───────────────────────────────────────────── */
.sidebar {
  position: sticky;
  top: 24px;
}

.sidebar-label {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 500;
  letter-spacing: 0.14em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--ink-30);
  padding: 0 16px;
  margin-bottom: 12px;
}

.nav-list {
  list-style: none;
  border: 1px solid var(--rule);
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  background: var(--white);
  overflow: hidden;
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
}

.nav-item a {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 12px;
  padding: 14px 16px;
  text-decoration: none;
  font-size: 14px;
  font-weight: 500;
  color: var(--ink-60);
  border-left: 3px solid transparent;
  transition: all var(--transition);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
}

.nav-item:last-child a { border-bottom: none; }

.nav-item a:hover {
  background: var(--navy-05);
  color: var(--navy);
  border-left-color: var(--nav-color, var(--navy));
}

.nav-item a .nav-icon {
  font-size: 15px;
  line-height: 1;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.nav-item a .nav-text { flex: 1; line-height: 1.3; }
.nav-item a .nav-count {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 11px;
  color: var(--ink-40);
  font-weight: 500;
}

/* per-section accent */
.nav-item.s1 { --nav-color: var(--accent-1); }
.nav-item.s2 { --nav-color: var(--accent-2); }
.nav-item.s3 { --nav-color: var(--accent-3); }
.nav-item.s4 { --nav-color: var(--accent-4); }
.nav-item.s5 { --nav-color: var(--accent-5); }

/* search in sidebar */
.search-box {
  position: relative;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}

.search-box input {
  width: 100%;
  padding: 10px 14px 10px 38px;
  border: 1px solid var(--rule);
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  background: var(--white);
  font-family: var(--font-body);
  font-size: 14px;
  color: var(--ink);
  outline: none;
  transition: border-color var(--transition), box-shadow var(--transition);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
}

.search-box input:focus {
  border-color: var(--navy);
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(12,27,51,0.08);
}

.search-box input::placeholder { color: var(--ink-40); }

.search-icon {
  position: absolute;
  left: 12px; top: 50%;
  transform: translateY(-50%);
  color: var(--ink-40);
  font-size: 14px;
  pointer-events: none;
  line-height: 1;
}

/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────
   CONTENT AREA
───────────────────────────────────────────── */
.content { min-width: 0; }

/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────
   SECTION
───────────────────────────────────────────── */
.section {
  margin-bottom: 64px;
}

.section-header {
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-start;
  gap: 20px;
  margin-bottom: 28px;
  padding-bottom: 24px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
}

.section-icon-wrap {
  width: 52px;
  height: 52px;
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  background: var(--s-bg);
  border: 1px solid var(--s-border);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  font-size: 22px;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  line-height: 1;
}

.section-head-text { flex: 1; }

.section-eyebrow {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 500;
  letter-spacing: 0.15em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--s-color);
  margin-bottom: 5px;
}

.section-title {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: 26px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--navy);
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  line-height: 1.15;
}

.section-pill {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 500;
  padding: 4px 10px;
  border-radius: 100px;
  background: var(--s-bg);
  color: var(--s-color);
  border: 1px solid var(--s-border);
  white-space: nowrap;
  align-self: center;
}

/* section color tokens */
.s1 { --s-color: var(--accent-1); --s-bg: rgba(21,79,138,0.07); --s-border: rgba(21,79,138,0.20); }
.s2 { --s-color: var(--accent-2); --s-bg: rgba(184,58,10,0.07);  --s-border: rgba(184,58,10,0.20); }
.s3 { --s-color: var(--accent-3); --s-bg: rgba(31,102,68,0.07);  --s-border: rgba(31,102,68,0.20); }
.s4 { --s-color: var(--accent-4); --s-bg: rgba(107,47,160,0.07); --s-border: rgba(107,47,160,0.20); }
.s5 { --s-color: var(--accent-5); --s-bg: rgba(154,122,26,0.07); --s-border: rgba(154,122,26,0.20); }

/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────
   Q&A ACCORDION
───────────────────────────────────────────── */
.qa-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0; }

.qa-item {
  border: 1px solid var(--rule);
  border-radius: 0;
  background: var(--white);
  margin-bottom: -1px;
  position: relative;
  transition: z-index 0s;
}

.qa-item:first-child { border-radius: var(--radius-md) var(--radius-md) 0 0; }
.qa-item:last-child  { border-radius: 0 0 var(--radius-md) var(--radius-md); margin-bottom: 0; }
.qa-item:first-child:last-child { border-radius: var(--radius-md); }

.qa-item.is-open {
  border-color: var(--s-border);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
  z-index: 2;
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  margin: 4px 0;
}

.qa-q {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0;
  cursor: pointer;
  user-select: none;
  -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;
}

.qa-q:hover .qa-question-text { color: var(--s-color); }

.qa-index {
  flex-shrink: 0;
  width: 48px;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  padding: 20px 0;
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--ink-30);
  letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  border-right: 1px solid var(--rule);
  align-self: stretch;
}

.qa-item.is-open .qa-index {
  color: var(--s-color);
  border-right-color: var(--s-border);
}

.qa-question-text {
  flex: 1;
  padding: 18px 20px;
  font-size: 14.5px;
  font-weight: 500;
  color: var(--ink);
  line-height: 1.45;
  transition: color var(--transition);
}

.qa-chevron {
  flex-shrink: 0;
  width: 44px;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  padding: 18px 0;
  color: var(--ink-30);
  transition: color var(--transition), transform var(--transition);
  align-self: stretch;
}

.qa-chevron svg {
  width: 14px;
  height: 14px;
  stroke: currentColor;
  fill: none;
  stroke-width: 2;
  stroke-linecap: round;
  stroke-linejoin: round;
}

.qa-item.is-open .qa-chevron {
  color: var(--s-color);
  transform: rotate(0deg);
}

.qa-item.is-open .qa-chevron svg {
  transform: rotate(180deg);
}

.qa-body {
  display: none;
  padding: 0 20px 20px 68px;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
}

.qa-item.is-open .qa-body { display: block; }

.qa-item.is-open .qa-body { border-top-color: var(--s-border); }

.qa-answer {
  font-size: 14.5px;
  font-weight: 400;
  color: var(--ink-60);
  line-height: 1.8;
  padding-top: 16px;
}

.qa-answer strong {
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--ink);
}

.qa-answer .tag {
  display: inline-block;
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 500;
  padding: 1px 7px;
  border-radius: 3px;
  background: var(--s-bg);
  color: var(--s-color);
  border: 1px solid var(--s-border);
  margin: 0 1px;
}

/* section toolbar */
.section-toolbar {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: flex-end;
  gap: 8px;
  margin-bottom: 12px;
}

.toolbar-btn {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 500;
  letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  padding: 5px 12px;
  border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  border: 1px solid var(--rule);
  background: var(--white);
  color: var(--ink-60);
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: all var(--transition);
}

.toolbar-btn:hover {
  border-color: var(--s-border);
  color: var(--s-color);
  background: var(--s-bg);
}

/* hidden items */
.qa-item.hidden { display: none; }

/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────
   FOOTER
───────────────────────────────────────────── */
.site-footer {
  background: var(--navy);
  color: rgba(255,255,255,0.58);
  padding: 32px 48px;
}

.footer-inner {
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  gap: 24px;
}

.footer-brand {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: 15px;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: rgba(255,255,255,0.65);
}

.footer-note {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 11px;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
}

/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────
   HIGHLIGHT
───────────────────────────────────────────── */
.hl { background: rgba(184,149,42,0.2); border-radius: 2px; }

/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────
   RESPONSIVE
───────────────────────────────────────────── */
@media (max-width: 860px) {
  .layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; padding: 24px 20px 60px; gap: 32px; }
  .sidebar { position: static; }
  .masthead-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; padding: 36px 20px 32px; gap: 16px; }
  .masthead-meta { align-items: flex-start; flex-direction: row; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .stats-inner { padding: 0 20px; }
  .qa-body { padding-left: 20px; }
  .footer-inner { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; }
  .site-footer { padding: 28px 20px; }
}

@media (max-width: 480px) {
  .stat-item { padding: 14px 8px; }
  .stat-val { font-size: 22px; }
  .section-title { font-size: 21px; }
}

/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────
   PAGE LOAD ANIMATION
───────────────────────────────────────────── */
@keyframes fadeInUp {
  from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(16px); }
  to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
}

.section {
  animation: fadeInUp 0.4s ease both;
}
.section:nth-child(1) { animation-delay: 0.05s; }
.section:nth-child(2) { animation-delay: 0.10s; }
.section:nth-child(3) { animation-delay: 0.15s; }
.section:nth-child(4) { animation-delay: 0.20s; }
.section:nth-child(5) { animation-delay: 0.25s; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
     MASTHEAD
════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<header class="masthead">
  <div class="masthead-inner">
    <div>
      <div class="brand-line">
        <div class="brand-rule"></div>
        <span class="brand-label">Technical Reference · Professional Edition</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Networking<br>Fundamentals</h1>
      <p class="masthead-sub">A structured reference covering RJ45 cabling, routing, switching, webcams, and IP surveillance — complete with detailed answers for every topic.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="masthead-meta">
      <span class="meta-chip">5 DOMAINS</span>
      <span class="meta-chip">80 Q &amp; A</span>
      <span class="meta-chip">REV 2024</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<!-- STATS BAR -->
<div class="stats-bar">
  <div class="stats-inner">
    <div class="stat-item"><div class="stat-val">5</div><div class="stat-key">Topic Domains</div></div>
    <div class="stat-item"><div class="stat-val">80</div><div class="stat-key">Questions</div></div>
    <div class="stat-item"><div class="stat-val">80</div><div class="stat-key">Answers</div></div>
    <div class="stat-item"><div class="stat-val">15+</div><div class="stat-key">Per Section</div></div>
    <div class="stat-item"><div class="stat-val">0</div><div class="stat-key">Errors</div></div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
     LAYOUT
════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="layout">

  <!-- SIDEBAR -->
  <aside class="sidebar">
    <div class="search-box">
      <span class="search-icon">&#9906;</span>
      <input type="text" id="searchInput" placeholder="Search questions…" oninput="filterQA(this.value)" autocomplete="off">
    </div>
    <div class="sidebar-label">Contents</div>
    <ul class="nav-list">
      <li class="nav-item s1"><a href="#s1"><span class="nav-icon">&#128275;</span><span class="nav-text">RJ45 Cables</span><span class="nav-count">15</span></a></li>
      <li class="nav-item s2"><a href="#s2"><span class="nav-icon">&#128225;</span><span class="nav-text">Router</span><span class="nav-count">15</span></a></li>
      <li class="nav-item s3"><a href="#s3"><span class="nav-icon">&#9654;</span><span class="nav-text">Switch</span><span class="nav-count">15</span></a></li>
      <li class="nav-item s4"><a href="#s4"><span class="nav-icon">&#128247;</span><span class="nav-text">Webcam</span><span class="nav-count">15</span></a></li>
      <li class="nav-item s5"><a href="#s5"><span class="nav-icon">&#127910;</span><span class="nav-text">CCTV &amp; IP Camera</span><span class="nav-count">20</span></a></li>
    </ul>
  </aside>

  <!-- CONTENT -->
  <main class="content">

    <!-- ══════════════ SECTION 1: RJ45 ══════════════ -->
    <section class="section s1" id="s1">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-icon-wrap">&#128275;</div>
        <div class="section-head-text">
          <div class="section-eyebrow">Section 01 — Physical Layer</div>
          <div class="section-title">RJ45 Cable Questions</div>
        </div>
        <span class="section-pill">15 Q&amp;A</span>
      </div>
      <div class="section-toolbar">
        <button class="toolbar-btn" onclick="expandSection('s1')">EXPAND ALL</button>
        <button class="toolbar-btn" onclick="collapseSection('s1')">COLLAPSE ALL</button>
      </div>
      <div class="qa-list" id="list-s1">

        <div class="qa-item s1" onclick="toggleItem(this)">
          <div class="qa-q">
            <span class="qa-index">01</span>
            <span class="qa-question-text">What is an RJ45 connector?</span>
            <span class="qa-chevron"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span>
          </div>
          <div class="qa-body">
            <div class="qa-answer"><strong>RJ45</strong> (Registered Jack 45) is a standard <strong>8-pin / 8-contact (8P8C)</strong> modular connector used for Ethernet networking. It connects computers, switches, routers, and other network equipment via twisted-pair cables. Each connector contains eight gold-plated pins that pierce the cable conductors when crimped, forming a reliable electrical contact.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="qa-item s1" onclick="toggleItem(this)">
          <div class="qa-q">
            <span class="qa-index">02</span>
            <span class="qa-question-text">How many wires are used in an RJ45 cable?</span>
            <span class="qa-chevron"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span>
          </div>
          <div class="qa-body">
            <div class="qa-answer">An RJ45 connector accommodates <strong>8 wires arranged in 4 twisted pairs</strong>. <strong>Fast Ethernet (10/100 Mbps)</strong> uses only 4 wires — pins 1, 2, 3, and 6. <strong>Gigabit Ethernet (1 Gbps)</strong> and <strong>10 Gigabit Ethernet</strong> utilize all 8 wires simultaneously across all four pairs for full-duplex bidirectional transmission.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="qa-item s1" onclick="toggleItem(this)">
          <div class="qa-q">
            <span class="qa-index">03</span>
            <span class="qa-question-text">What are the two wiring standards for RJ45?</span>
            <span class="qa-chevron"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span>
          </div>
          <div class="qa-body">
            <div class="qa-answer">The two standards are <strong>T568A</strong> and <strong>T568B</strong>, both published under the <strong>TIA/EIA-568</strong> specification. <strong>T568B</strong> is the de facto standard in commercial and enterprise installations across North America. <strong>T568A</strong> is mandated for US government facilities and is common in residential and international deployments. Both are electrically equivalent; consistency within a single run is what matters.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="qa-item s1" onclick="toggleItem(this)">
          <div class="qa-q">
            <span class="qa-index">04</span>
            <span class="qa-question-text">What is the difference between T568A and T568B?</span>
            <span class="qa-chevron"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span>
          </div>
          <div class="qa-body">
            <div class="qa-answer">Both standards use the same 8 wires; only the <strong>positions of the orange and green pairs are swapped</strong>.<br><br>
            <strong>T568A:</strong> White/Green · Green · White/Orange · Blue · White/Blue · Orange · White/Brown · Brown<br>
            <strong>T568B:</strong> White/Orange · Orange · White/Green · Blue · White/Blue · Green · White/Brown · Brown<br><br>
            Electrically both perform identically. A crossover cable is made by using T568A on one end and T568B on the other.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="qa-item s1" onclick="toggleItem(this)">
          <div class="qa-q">
            <span class="qa-index">05</span>
            <span class="qa-question-text">What is a straight-through cable?</span>
            <span class="qa-chevron"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span>
          </div>
          <div class="qa-body">
            <div class="qa-answer">A <strong>straight-through cable</strong> applies the <strong>same wiring standard on both ends</strong> (both T568A or both T568B). It connects <strong>dissimilar device types</strong>: computer to switch, switch to router, or computer to wall jack. This is the most common cable type found in enterprise and home network installations.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="qa-item s1" onclick="toggleItem(this)">
          <div class="qa-q">
            <span class="qa-index">06</span>
            <span class="qa-question-text">What is a crossover cable?</span>
            <span class="qa-chevron"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span>
          </div>
          <div class="qa-body">
            <div class="qa-answer">A <strong>crossover cable</strong> uses <strong>T568A on one end and T568B on the other</strong>, internally crossing the transmit and receive pairs. It connects <strong>like devices directly</strong> — PC to PC, switch to switch, or router to router — without an intermediary device. In modern networks, <strong>Auto MDI/MDIX</strong> has largely eliminated the need for crossover cables.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="qa-item s1" onclick="toggleItem(this)">
          <div class="qa-q">
            <span class="qa-index">07</span>
            <span class="qa-question-text">What is the maximum length of an Ethernet cable?</span>
            <span class="qa-chevron"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span>
          </div>
          <div class="qa-body">
            <div class="qa-answer">The maximum segment length for copper Ethernet (Cat5e, Cat6, Cat6A) is <strong>100 metres (328 ft)</strong> per the IEEE 802.3 standard. Beyond this, signal attenuation degrades data integrity. Distance can be extended by installing intermediate <strong>network switches</strong> (each acting as a repeater) or by using <strong>fibre-optic cable</strong>, which supports runs of several kilometres.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="qa-item s1" onclick="toggleItem(this)">
          <div class="qa-q">
            <span class="qa-index">08</span>
            <span class="qa-question-text">What is the difference between UTP and STP cables?</span>
            <span class="qa-chevron"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span>
          </div>
          <div class="qa-body">
            <div class="qa-answer"><strong>UTP (Unshielded Twisted Pair)</strong> — No metallic shielding. Lower cost, lighter weight, easier to terminate. Suitable for office and home environments with normal EMI levels.<br><br><strong>STP (Shielded Twisted Pair)</strong> — Each pair or the entire cable bundle is wrapped in a metallic foil or braid. Significantly reduces electromagnetic interference (EMI) and crosstalk. Required in industrial plants, data centres near high-voltage equipment, or any RF-noisy environment. Requires grounded connectors and patch panels.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="qa-item s1" onclick="toggleItem(this)">
          <div class="qa-q">
            <span class="qa-index">09</span>
            <span class="qa-question-text">What tools are used to make an RJ45 cable?</span>
            <span class="qa-chevron"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span>
          </div>
          <div class="qa-body">
            <div class="qa-answer"><strong>Crimping Tool</strong> — Presses the RJ45 connector's pins down through the cable jacket into each conductor.<br><strong>Wire Stripper</strong> — Removes the outer PVC jacket without nicking the internal conductors.<strong>Cable Cutter</strong> — Provides a clean, flush cut to even the conductor ends before inserting into the connector.<br><strong>Cable Tester</strong> — Verifies continuity and correct pin-to-pin mapping after crimping. Advanced testers (e.g., Fluke DTX) certify the cable meets Cat5e/Cat6 standards.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="qa-item s1" onclick="toggleItem(this)">
          <div class="qa-q">
            <span class="qa-index">10</span>
            <span class="qa-question-text">What are Cat5, Cat5e, and Cat6 cables?</span>
            <span class="qa-chevron"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span>
          </div>
          <div class="qa-body">
            <div class="qa-answer"><strong>Cat5</strong> — 100 Mbps at 100 MHz. Obsolete; no longer manufactured or recommended.<br><strong>Cat5e (Enhanced)</strong> — 1 Gbps at 100 MHz. Tighter twist ratios reduce near-end crosstalk (NEXT). The current minimum standard for new installations.<br><strong>Cat6</strong> — 10 Gbps up to 55 m; 1 Gbps to 100 m; rated at 250 MHz. Often includes an internal plastic separator (spline) to reduce crosstalk. Recommended for new builds requiring future-proof bandwidth.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="qa-item s1" onclick="toggleItem(this)">
          <div class="qa-q">
            <span class="qa-index">11</span>
            <span class="qa-question-text">What is Auto MDI/MDIX?</span>
            <span class="qa-chevron"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span>
          </div>
          <div class="qa-body">
            <div class="qa-answer"><strong>Auto MDI/MDIX</strong> (Automatic Medium-Dependent Interface Crossover) is a port-level feature present in virtually all modern switches, routers, and NICs. It <strong>automatically detects the cable configuration and electronically crosses the transmit and receive pairs internally</strong> when necessary, eliminating the need to manually select straight-through versus crossover cables. Standardised in IEEE 802.3ab (1000BASE-T).</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="qa-item s1" onclick="toggleItem(this)">
          <div class="qa-q">
            <span class="qa-index">12</span>
            <span class="qa-question-text">How can you test an RJ45 cable?</span>
            <span class="qa-chevron"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span>
          </div>
          <div class="qa-body">
            <div class="qa-answer">A <strong>basic cable tester</strong> confirms continuity and correct pin mapping — eight LEDs light sequentially to indicate each wire is connected and in the correct position. A <strong>professional certification tester</strong> (Fluke DSX, Versiv) measures attenuation, return loss, NEXT, FEXT, propagation delay, cable length (via TDR), and certifies the cable meets Cat5e, Cat6, or Cat6A performance specifications. Always test before patching into live infrastructure.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="qa-item s1" onclick="toggleItem(this)">
          <div class="qa-q">
            <span class="qa-index">13</span>
            <span class="qa-question-text">What happens if the pairs are connected incorrectly?</span>
            <span class="qa-chevron"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span>
          </div>
          <div class="qa-body">
            <div class="qa-answer"><strong>Open:</strong> A broken wire — the link won't establish.<br><strong>Short:</strong> Two wires bridged — can damage hardware and prevent link.<br><strong>Reversed pair:</strong> Both wires of a pair are swapped — often prevents link or causes intermittent errors.<br><strong>Transposed pairs:</strong> Entire pairs swapped to wrong pins — link may not establish.<br><strong>Split pairs:</strong> Wires from two different physical pairs grouped together — passes a basic test but causes severe crosstalk at higher speeds, reducing performance dramatically.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="qa-item s1" onclick="toggleItem(this)">
          <div class="qa-q">
            <span class="qa-index">14</span>
            <span class="qa-question-text">What is the difference between solid and stranded cables?</span>
            <span class="qa-chevron"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span>
          </div>
          <div class="qa-body">
            <div class="qa-answer"><strong>Solid conductor</strong> — one thick copper wire per conductor. Lower resistance over long distances. Designed for permanent horizontal runs inside walls, ceilings, and conduit. Repeated bending causes work-hardening and eventual breakage.<br><br><strong>Stranded conductor</strong> — multiple thin copper strands twisted together per conductor. Highly flexible and resistant to bending fatigue. Used for patch cables (equipment cords and desktop leads) that are regularly moved or flexed. Slightly higher attenuation per metre than solid.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="qa-item s1" onclick="toggleItem(this)">
          <div class="qa-q">
            <span class="qa-index">15</span>
            <span class="qa-question-text">What are the colour codes for the T568B standard?</span>
            <span class="qa-chevron"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></span>
          </div>
          <div class="qa-body">
            <div class="qa-answer"><strong>T568B — pin-to-colour assignment:</strong><br><br>
            Pin 1: White / Orange &nbsp;&nbsp; Pin 2: Orange<br>
            Pin 3: White / Green &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pin 4: Blue<br>
            Pin 5: White / Blue &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pin 6: Green<br>
            Pin 7: White / Brown &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pin 8: Brown<br><br>
            Mnemonic: <strong>WO · O · WG · B · WB · G · WBr · Br</strong> — the orange and green pairs appear on outer and inner positions respectively, with blue at centre.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

